#. type: Content of: <included><section><title>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "Finalizing the Installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><note>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:15
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <b>total</b> elapsed time between the display of the boot prompt on the\n"
"minimal CD and the display of the login prompt after the reboot was\n"
"<b>00:42:31</b> on our test box. Yes, less than one hour! Note that this time\n"
"also includes the stage3, Portage snapshot and several packages download time\n"
"and the time spent configuring the kernel.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:23
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Log in as <c>root</c>, then add one or more users for daily use with\n"
"<c>useradd</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <included><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "Connect to your new box from another PC"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:28
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Clean up your known_hosts file because your new box\n"
"has generated a new definitive hostkey)</comment>\n"
"$ <i>nano -w ~/.ssh/known_hosts</i>\n"
"<comment>(Look for the IP of your new PC and delete the line,\n"
"then save the file and exit nano)</comment>\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Use the IP address of your new box)</comment>\n"
"$ <i>ssh root@192.168.1.10</i>\n"
"The authenticity of host '192.168.1.10 (192.168.1.10)' can't be established.\n"
"RSA key fingerprint is 96:e7:2d:12:ac:9c:b0:94:90:9f:40:89:b0:45:26:8f.\n"
"Are you sure you want to continue connecting (yes/no)? <i>yes</i>\n"
"Warning: Permanently added '192.168.1.10' (RSA) to the list of known hosts.\n"
"Password: <comment>type_the_password</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <included><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:43
#, no-wrap
msgid "Add a new user"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:44
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mybox ~ # <i>useradd -g users -G lp,wheel,audio,cdrom,portage,cron -m john</i>\n"
"mybox ~ # <i>passwd john</i>\n"
"New UNIX password: <comment>Set John's password</comment>\n"
"Retype new UNIX password: <comment>Type John's password again</comment>\n"
"passwd: password updated successfully\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><title>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:54
#, no-wrap
msgid "Last configuration touches"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:58
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Start by selecting nearby mirrors either by defining the <c>SYNC</c> and\n"
"<c>GENTOO_MIRRORS</c> variables in <path>/etc/portage/make.conf</path> or by using\n"
"<c>mirrorselect</c>. You can also define the number of concurrent compilation\n"
"processes at this point.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <included><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:64
#, no-wrap
msgid "Use mirrorselect and set MAKEOPTS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:65
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mybox ~ # <i>emerge mirrorselect</i>\n"
"mybox ~ # <i>mirrorselect -i -o >> /etc/portage/make.conf</i>\n"
"mybox ~ # <i>mirrorselect -i -r -o >> /etc/portage/make.conf</i>\n"
"<comment>(Usually, (the number of processors + 1) is a good value)</comment>\n"
"mybox ~ # <i>echo 'MAKEOPTS=\"-j2\"' >> /etc/portage/make.conf</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:73
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now is a good time to enable or disable some USE flags. Run <c>emerge -vpe\n"
"world</c> to list all currently installed packages and their enabled and\n"
"disabled USE flags. Either edit <path>/etc/portage/make.conf</path> or use the\n"
"following command to define the USE variable:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <included><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:79
#, no-wrap
msgid "View USE flags in use and enable or disable some"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:80
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mybox ~ # <i>emerge -vpe world</i>\n"
"<comment>(Portage displays the packages and their USE flags, as an example, let's\n"
"disable fortran, and enable ipv6 and unicode)</comment>\n"
"mybox ~ # <i>echo 'USE=\"nptl nptlonly ipv6 -fortran unicode\"' >> /etc/portage/make.conf</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:87
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Recent versions of glibc use <path>/etc/locale.gen</path> to define locale\n"
"settings.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <included><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:91
#, no-wrap
msgid "Define locales"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:92
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mybox ~ # <i>cd /etc</i>\n"
"mybox etc # <i>nano -w locale.gen</i>\n"
"mybox etc # <i>locale-gen</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:98
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Last but not least, you may want to alter the <c>CFLAGS</c> variable in your\n"
"<path>/etc/portage/make.conf</path> to optimise the code to your specific needs. Please\n"
"note that using a long list of flags is rarely needed and can even lead to a\n"
"broken system. It is recommended to specify the processor type in the\n"
"<c>march</c> option and stick to <c>-O2 -pipe</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:106
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You may also want to switch to <b>~x86</b>. You should only do this if you can\n"
"deal with the odd broken ebuild or package. If you'd rather keep your system\n"
"stable, <e>don't</e> add the <c>ACCEPT_KEYWORDS</c> variable.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <included><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:111
#, no-wrap
msgid "Last edit of make.conf"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:112
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mybox etc # <i>cd portage</i>\n"
"mybox portage # <i>nano -w make.conf</i>\n"
"<comment>(Set -march to your CPU type in CFLAGS)</comment>\n"
"CFLAGS=\"-O2 -march=<i>athlon-xp</i> -pipe\"\n"
"<comment>(Only add the following if you know what you're doing)</comment>\n"
"ACCEPT_KEYWORDS=\"~x86\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:121
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You might want to recompile your whole system twice to make full use of your\n"
"latest configuration changes. It would take quite a long time to complete and\n"
"yield minimal speed benefits. You can let your system optimise itself gradually\n"
"over time when new versions of packages are released. However, recompiling is\n"
"a still good idea from the standpoint of maintaining system consistency. Please\n"
"see the <uri link=\"/doc/en/gcc-upgrading.xml\">Gentoo GCC Upgrading Guide</uri>\n"
"for a discussion on the benefits of ensuring a consistently built system and\n"
"world.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:132
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Recompiling only the packages that have already been updated since the release\n"
"or that are affected by your new USE flags will take enough time.  You might\n"
"also have to remove packages that block your upgrade. Look for \"[blocks\n"
"<brite>B</brite>     ]\" in the output of <c>emerge -vpuD --newuse world</c> and\n"
"use <c>emerge -C</c> to remove them.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <included><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:139
#, no-wrap
msgid "Update your packages"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:140
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Please note that the switch to ~x86 causes many packages to be upgraded)</comment>\n"
"mybox etc # <i>emerge -vpuD --newuse world</i>\n"
"<comment>(Take a good look at the package list and their USE flags,\n"
"remove blocking packages if any, and start the lengthy process)</comment>\n"
"mybox etc # <i>time emerge -vuD --newuse world</i>\n"
"<comment>(79 packages have been (re)compiled)</comment>\n"
"\n"
"real  180m13.276s\n"
"user  121m22.905s\n"
"sys   36m31.472s\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Remerge libtool to avoid further potential problems)</comment>\n"
"mybox etc # <i>emerge --oneshot libtool</i>\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Update config files, make sure you <b>do not</b> let dispatch-conf\n"
"update config files you have edited)</comment>\n"
"mybox etc # <i>dispatch-conf</i>\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(If perl has been updated, you should run the perl-cleaner script)</comment>\n"
"mybox etc # <i>time perl-cleaner all</i>\n"
"real  1m6.495s\n"
"user  0m42.699s\n"
"sys   0m10.641s\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(In case of a major upgrade of python, you should run the python-updater script)</comment>\n"
"mybox etc # <i>python-updater</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><title>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:171
#, no-wrap
msgid "What to do next"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:175
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Depending on what your new Gentoo machine is supposed to do, you will probably\n"
"want to install server applications or a desktop system. Just as an example,\n"
"<c>emerge gnome</c> and <c>emerge kde</c> have been timed on the ~x86 system\n"
"installed as describe above. Both have been installed from the same starting\n"
"point.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:183
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You should check our <uri link=\"/doc/en/\">documentation index</uri> to find out\n"
"how to install and configure the applications of your choice.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><impo>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:188
#, no-wrap
msgid "The following is only an example. It is in no way meant as a recommended setup.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <included><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:191
#, no-wrap
msgid "Emerge GNOME"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:192
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mybox etc # <i>emerge -vp gnome</i>\n"
"<comment>(Look at the list of packages and their USE flags,\n"
"then edit make.conf if required.</comment>\n"
"mybox etc # <i>nano -w /etc/portage/make.conf</i>\n"
"<comment>(The following USE flags have been defined)</comment>\n"
"USE=\"-fortran dbus -kde -qt4 -eds \"\n"
"\n"
"mybox etc # <i>time emerge gnome</i>\n"
"<comment>(326 packages have been emerged)</comment>\n"
"\n"
"real  520m44.532s\n"
"user  339m21.144s\n"
"sys   146m22.337s\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <included><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:207
#, no-wrap
msgid "Emerge KDE"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <included><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-x86-quickinstall-after-reboot.xml:208
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mybox etc # <i>emerge -vp kde-meta</i>\n"
"<comment>(Look at the list of packages and their USE flags,\n"
"then edit make.conf if required.</comment>\n"
"mybox etc # <i>nano -w /etc/portage/make.conf</i>\n"
"<comment>The following USE flags have been defined)</comment>\n"
"USE=\"-fortran -eds -gnome -gstreamer -gtk -firefox\"\n"
"\n"
"mybox etc # <i>time emerge kde-meta</i>\n"
"<comment>(391 packages have been emerged)</comment>\n"
"\n"
"real  1171m25.318s\n"
"user  851m26.393s\n"
"sys   281m45.629s\n"
msgstr ""
